        "heading": "1.6 Colligative Properties",
        "body": "<p>or in terms of molar mass</p>\n<p>The properties of solutions which depend only on the number of solute particles irrespective of their nature relative to the total number of particles present in the solution, are called colligative properties.</p>\n<p>(Colligative : From Latin : Co means together, ligare means to bind.)</p>\n<p>There are four important colligative properties ● relative lowering of vapour pressure, ● elevation in boiling point, ● depression in freezing point and ● osmotic pressure of solution.</p>\n<p>(Neglecting rij in denominator)</p>\n<p>n1</p>\n<p>Pi</p>\n<p>M2 XW 1</p>\n<p>where, Wj and W2 are the masses and M, and M2 are the molar masses of the solvent and solute, respectively.</p>",
