              "type": "theory",
              "q": "(a) Identify anode/cathode in galvanic cell using electrochemical series. (b) Role of salt bridge. (c) Advantage and disadvantage of fuel cell.",
              "explain": "Model answer: (a) Half-cell with lower (more negative) E° is the anode (oxidation); higher E° is the cathode (reduction). (b) Salt bridge maintains electrical neutrality and completes the circuit by allowing ion flow without mixing the two solutions. (c) Advantage: high efficiency, eco-friendly (water is the only product for H₂/O₂). Disadvantage: high cost of catalysts (Pt) and infrastructure for fuel storage.",
