              "type": "theory",
              "q": "(a) Why does specific conductance decrease on dilution? (b) Why must emf be positive for spontaneous reaction? (c) Name a cell whose reaction cannot be reversed; one disadvantage.",
              "explain": "Model answer: (a) On dilution, the number of ions per unit volume decreases ⇒ specific conductance (κ) falls. (Molar conductivity rises.) (b) ΔG = −nFE; for spontaneity ΔG < 0 ⇒ E > 0. (c) Primary cell, e.g., dry cell. Disadvantage: cannot be recharged once exhausted (single use).",
