        "heading": "2.2 Electrochemical Series",
        "body": "<p>The arrangement of various standard half-cells in the order of their decreasing values of standard reduction potentials is called electrochemical series or activity series or electromotive series.</p>\n<p>u (/i</p>\n<p>c &lt;/&gt;</p>\n<p>&lt;u</p>\n<p>c</p>\n<p>2H'\" +2e\"</p>\n<p>I O j= to</p>\n<p>c V C/)</p>\n<p>b.</p>\n<p>u</p>\n<p>● Negative E° means that the redox couple is stronger reducing agent than e.g., Zn (-0.76 V). ● Positive £° means that the redox couple is a weaker reducing agent than e.g., Ag (-F 0.80 V).</p>",
