        "heading": "2.8 Fuel Cells",
        "body": "<p>■&gt; 40H (aq)</p>\n<p>&gt; 2H2O (/)</p>\n<p>Advantages of Fuel Cells Some of the advantages of fuel cells are as follows. ● It is highly efficient (70%) as compared to thermal power plants (40%). ● It does not cause pollution as no harmful products are formed.</p>\n<p>● This cell runs as long as the reactants are supplied. ● This cell being light weight have been used in automobiles on an experimental basis.</p>\n<p>Disadvantages of Fuel Cells ● Difficulty is faced in handling the gaseous fuels. ● Catalysts used are very costly. ● Electrode preparation is very difficult and time taking.</p>",
