              "id": "we_chem_7_T10_1",
              "prompt": "Order acidity: water, ethanol, phenol. Justify.",
              "steps": [
                "Phenoxide (from phenol) is resonance-stabilised by the aromatic ring.",
                "Hydroxide and ethoxide have no such delocalisation.",
                "Among water and ethanol, ethanol is slightly less acidic because –C₂H₅ is electron-donating (+I).",
                "Hence: phenol > water > ethanol in acidity."
              ],
              "finalAnswer": "Phenol > water > ethanol (phenoxide is resonance-stabilised).",
              "_source": "Authored from NCERT/ISC pattern"
